      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 1: Create sample data\n",
        "countries = ['India', 'China', 'USA', 'Indonesia', 'Pakistan', 'Brazil', 'Nigeria']\n",
        "population = [1420, 1410, 339, 276, 240, 215, 223]  # Population in millions\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 2: Plotting the bar chart\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))  # Set the figure size\n",
        "plt.bar(countries, population, color='orange')  # Bar color\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 3: Add title and labels\n",
        "plt.title('Population Distribution by Country', fontsize=16)\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Country', fontsize=12)\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Population (in millions)', fontsize=12)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 4: Add grid for better readability\n",
        "plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 5: Show the plot\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    }
  ]
